o:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc98dc136-2ff5-44bc-ab5f-2bed82ae47cb_675x1024.jpeg\" style=\"border: none;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;margin: 0 auto;width: auto;height: auto;max-width: 100%\" width=\"550\"></a></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\">In the latest installment of Tough Love, a stay-at-home father of four writes to Abigail Shrier asking if progressive gender ideas have emasculated him. His brothers-in-law jet around the world and close deals while their wives handle the kids, and he can&#8217;t shake the feeling that he&#8217;s being left behind. Read our advice columnist&#8217;s response to Martin, 44, and all diaper-changing dads.</div></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"button-fZfkQf\" style=\"color: #f2312c;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .1em;font-family: Arial,sans-serif;font-weight: 700;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><a class=\"buttonMd-Lg5kyv\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/b2b4c105-4310-4118-864c-225b1504e6ec?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"font-size: 16px;color: #f2312c;text-decoration: none;\">Read full story</a></div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"digestPostEmbed-flwiST custom-css-email-digest-post-embed\" data-component-name=\"DigestPostEmbedStatic\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;padding: 0;position: relative;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"width:100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><a class=\"link-AiRTNr\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/70975ba9-f1de-4dd0-8f23-f47373032f6a?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;color: #161613;\"><div class=\"title-RKep04\" style=\"line-height: 1.1;color: #161613;font-family: Arial,sans-serif;font-weight: 700;font-size: 24px\">Let the Kids Smoke</div></a></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><div class=\"meta-XhipYq\" style=\"font-size: 14px;line-height: 1;color: #7d858b;letter-spacing: .1em;text-transform: uppercase;font-family: Arial,sans-serif;font-weight: 700;\"><a class=\"inheritColor-eP1Bab\" href=\"https://substack.com/profile/370458680-kara-kennedy\" style=\"color: inherit;text-decoration: none;\">Kara Kennedy</a></div></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/70975ba9-f1de-4dd0-8f23-f47373032f6a?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><img alt=\"Let the Kids Smoke\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!ajSS!,w_1100,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a6c02c9-4b71-419d-bdb5-b0a1c262af2e_1024x671.jpeg\" style=\"border: none;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;margin: 0 auto;width: auto;height: auto;max-width: 100%\" width=\"550\"></a></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\">Britain just banned anyone born after 2008 from ever buying tobacco, and Kara Kennedy, who spent her teenage years sneaking cigarettes behind her school building in Wales, thinks the next generation is being robbed of the chance to make their own mistakes. Read her column on what&#8217;s lost after this draconian smoking ban.</div></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"button-fZfkQf\" style=\"color: #f2312c;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .1em;font-family: Arial,sans-serif;font-weight: 700;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><a class=\"buttonMd-Lg5kyv\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/70975ba9-f1de-4dd0-8f23-f47373032f6a?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"font-size: 16px;color: #f2312c;text-decoration: none;\">Read full story</a></div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"digestPostEmbed-flwiST custom-css-email-digest-post-embed\" data-component-name=\"DigestPostEmbedStatic\" style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;padding: 0;position: relative;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"width:100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><a class=\"link-AiRTNr\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/0c3495c0-8b35-4b2d-a782-f0353246d201?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;color: #161613;\"><div class=\"title-RKep04\" style=\"line-height: 1.1;color: #161613;font-family: Arial,sans-serif;font-weight: 700;font-size: 24px\">The Ten Commandments Don&#8217;t Belong in Public School</div></a></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><div class=\"meta-XhipYq\" style=\"font-size: 14px;line-height: 1;color: #7d858b;letter-spacing: .1em;text-transform: uppercase;font-family: Arial,sans-serif;font-weight: 700;\"><a class=\"inheritColor-eP1Bab\" href=\"https://substack.com/profile/250304972-jed-rubenfeld\" style=\"color: inherit;text-decoration: none;\">Jed Rubenfeld</a></div></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/0c3495c0-8b35-4b2d-a782-f0353246d201?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><img alt=\"The Ten Commandments Don&#8217;t Belong in Public School\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!NXJy!,w_1100,c_fill,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep,g_auto/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0b759b91-6f98-463b-9553-42e2ee686ab5_1024x683.jpeg\" style=\"border: none;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;margin: 0 auto;width: auto;height: auto;max-width: 100%\" width=\"550\"></a></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><div style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\">Should the Ten Commandments hang in American public school classrooms? A federal appeals court just said yes, but Jed Rubenfeld thinks the ruling opens the door for any state to post the religious text of its choice in schools. The issue is not the Ten Commandments specifically. The same principles that keep political ideology out of classrooms should keep scripture out too.</div></td></tr><tr height=\"16\"><td></td></tr><tr><td><table role=\"presentation\" width=\"auto\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><div class=\"button-fZfkQf\" style=\"color: #f2312c;text-transform: uppercase;letter-spacing: .1em;font-family: Arial,sans-serif;font-weight: 700;font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;\"><a class=\"buttonMd-Lg5kyv\" href=\"https://substack.com/redirect/0c3495c0-8b35-4b2d-a782-f0353246d201?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8\" style=\"font-size: 16px;color: #f2312c;text-decoration: none;\">Read full story</a></div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table></div><h5 style=\"font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Baskerville, serif !important;font-weight: bold !important;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased